== 财政大臣 ==
[[File:George_osborne_hi.jpg|thumb]]
=== 削减政府开支（2010年） ===

奥斯本于2010年5月11日被任命为[[财政大臣_(英国)|财政大臣]]，根据内阁大臣的传统，第二天他宣誓就职[[枢密院顾问官|枢密院顾问官]]。<ref name="pc-13may2010">{{cite web|url=http://www.privy-council.org.uk/files/other/13th%20May2010%20List.doc |title=Privy Council Orders |trans_title=枢密院排名|date=13 May 2010 |publisher=Privy Council |accessdate=26 July 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110611044054/http://www.privy-council.org.uk/files/other/13th%20May2010%20List.doc |archivedate=11 June 2011 }}</ref>奥斯本在[[2008年金融危机|金融危机]]持续的时候成为财政大臣。他上任后立即采取的行动有两个，即设立{{le|预算责任办公室|Office for Budget Responsibility}}和进行政府范围的{{le|支出审查|2010 Spending Review}}，于2010年秋季完成，所有政府部门2014-15年度之后的开支计划不被批准。<ref name="FT_10062010">{{cite news|title=A question for chancellor Osborne|trans_title=奥斯本财相的问题|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/31d8576e-74c6-11df-aed7-00144feabdc0.html|accessdate=10 June 2011|newspaper=Financial Times|date=10 June 2010|author=Martin Wolf|archive-date=2010-12-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101228081939/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/31d8576e-74c6-11df-aed7-00144feabdc0.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>在2010年大选之前不久，奥斯本曾承诺要对英国的预算赤字进行“比[[撒切尔夫人|撒切尔]]更强硬”的削减，<ref name="BBC Thatcher">{{Cite web | title = Osborne will be 'tougher than Thatcher' | trans_title = 奥斯本将比“撒切尔更强硬” | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/today/hi/today/newsid_8536000/8536028.stm | website = Today (BBC Radio 4) | publisher = [[BBC_Radio_4|BBC Radio 4]] | date = 25 February 2010 | accessdate = 15 May 2015 | archive-date = 2015-05-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150518103450/http://news.bbc.co.uk/today/hi/today/newsid_8536000/8536028.stm | dead-url = no }}</ref>他正确地设定了减少英国赤字的目标，以至于在2015-16年财政年度，公共债务总额将下降为GDP的一小部分。<ref name="STelegraph_12062011">{{cite news|title=UK economy 'Plan A' – Is George Osborne on the right path?|trans_title=英国经济的“A计划” - 乔治·奥斯本在正确的道路上？|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/economics/8570045/UK-economy-Plan-A-Is-George-Osborne-on-the-right-path.html|accessdate=12 June 2011|newspaper=The Sunday Telegraph|date=12 June 2011|author=Emma Rowley|archive-date=2020-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122154227/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/economics/8570045/UK-economy-Plan-A-Is-George-Osborne-on-the-right-path.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2010年5月24日，奥斯本公布了62亿英镑的削减：“我们根本不能每周增加30亿英镑的公共债务。”<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/8699522.stm |title=George Osborne outlines detail of £6.2bn spending cuts |trans_title=乔治·奥斯本概述了62亿英镑支出削减的细节 |publisher=BBC News |date=24 May 2010 |accessdate=2017-01-28 |archive-date=2017-08-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170830020537/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/8699522.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>当年6月泄漏的财政部文件透露，奥斯本预计他的更严格的开支削减计划将导致在本届议会任期内（五年），全国失去130万份工作机会。<ref name="Guardian_29062010">{{cite news|title=Budget will cost 1.3m jobs – Treasury|trans_title=财政部：预算削减将导致130万个就业岗位消失|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk/2010/jun/29/budget-job-losses-unemployment-austerity|accessdate=10 June 2011|newspaper=The Guardian|date=29 June 2010|author=Larry Elliott|quote=还未公布的二战以来最严格的公共开支削减计划估计：2015年前，大约有60万个公共部门的就业机会和70万个私营部门的就业机会将消失。 . . . 上周预算演示文稿最终版本的幻灯片。 . . . 大约每年有12万个公共部门和14万个私营部门的工作岗位消失。 |archive-date=2013-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002154155/http://www.theguardian.com/uk/2010/jun/29/budget-job-losses-unemployment-austerity|dead-url=no}}</ref>奥斯本称他的反对者为“赤字否认者”。<ref name="CoffeeHouse_10062011">{{cite web|title=Barber, Blanchflower and the fake debate on double dip |trans_title=二次触底的假辩论|url=http://www.spectator.co.uk/coffeehouse/6270798/barber-blanchflower-and-the-fake-debate-on-double-dip.html |work=Coffee House |location=UK |accessdate=10 June 2011 |author=Ed Howker |date=14 September 2010 }}{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

2010年7月，奥斯本，寻求削减高达25％的政府支出来解决赤字，价值20亿英镑的四艘[[前鋒級彈道飛彈潛艇|前卫级弹道导弹核潜艇]]的建造项目被[[英国国防部|国防部]]视为核心项目，奥斯本的削减计划意味着这一项目的剩余预算被大大削减。国防大臣[[利亚姆·福克斯|利亚姆·福克斯]]警告说，如果[[三叉戟飛彈|三叉戟]]被视为核心经费，就必须严格限制英国军事行动的方式。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/politics/defence/7916513/George-Osborne-Trident-is-not-exempt-from-budget-cuts.html |title=George Osborne: Trident is not exempt from budget cuts |trans_title=乔治·奥斯本：三叉戟不能幸免于削减 |work=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |date=29 July 2010 |accessdate=4 October 2010 |first=Rosa |last=Prince |archive-date=2010-08-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100802002716/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/politics/defence/7916513/George-Osborne-Trident-is-not-exempt-from-budget-cuts.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

奥斯本在10月20日提交了政府的支出审查，其中为每个政府部门制定的固定支出预算到2014-15年为止。<ref>{{cite web|title=Key Spending Review announcements |trans_title=关键支出审查公告|work=Spending Review |url=http://www.hm-treasury.gov.uk/spend_sr2010_keyannouncements.htm |publisher=HM Treasury |accessdate=10 June 2011 |date=22 November 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110518143005/http://hm-treasury.gov.uk/spend_sr2010_keyannouncements.htm |archivedate=18 May 2011 }}</ref><ref name=BBC_21102010>{{cite news|title=Spending Review 2010: Key points at-a-glance|trans_title=2010年支出回顾：关键点一览|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-11569160|accessdate=10 June 2011|publisher=BBC News|date=21 October 2010|archive-date=2020-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123184600/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-11569160|dead-url=no}}</ref>在成为财政大臣之前和之后，奥斯本声称英国处于“破产的边缘”，<ref name=Times_25112008>{{cite news|title=Parties reveal their battle lines for the next election|trans_title=各方公布他们下次大选的纲领|url=http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/economics/pbr/article5226636.ece|accessdate=11 June 2011|newspaper=The Times|date=25 November 2008|author=Sam Coates|archive-date=2011-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110809040301/http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/economics/pbr/article5226636.ece|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Guardian_04102010>{{cite news|title=George Osborne's speech to the Conservative party conference in full|trans_title=秋天保守党年会上奥斯本的演讲|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/oct/04/george-osborne-speech-conservative-conference|accessdate=11 June 2011|newspaper=The Guardian|date=4 October 2010|author=George Osborne|archive-date=2013-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002164909/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/oct/04/george-osborne-speech-conservative-conference|dead-url=no}}</ref>虽然这一说法被{{le|财政专责委员会|Treasury Select Committee}}和其他人批评为试图证明其支出削减计划的合理性。<ref name=FT_20102010>{{cite news|author=Martin Wolf|authorlink=Martin Wolf|date=20 October 2010|title=A spending review for a diminished country|trans_title=减少国家的支出审查|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/ac9815ca-dc4a-11df-a9a4-00144feabdc0.html|work=[[金融时报_(英国)|金融时报]]|accessdate=30 September 2013|quote=The chancellor presents the hypothesis of looming national 'bankruptcy'. If so, the UK must have been bankrupt for much of the past two centuries.|archive-date=2011-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110128200524/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/ac9815ca-dc4a-11df-a9a4-00144feabdc0.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Guardian_04112010>{{cite web|author=Phillip Inman|date=4 November 2010|title=George Osborne accused of misleading public over UK bankruptcy claim|trans_title=乔治·奥斯本的英国破产言论被指控误导公众|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/nov/04/george-osborne-misleading-crisis-claims|work=[[卫报|卫报]]|accessdate=30 September 2013|archive-date=2013-12-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219130512/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/nov/04/george-osborne-misleading-crisis-claims|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2010年10月4日，在[[伯明翰|伯明翰]]保守党年会的一次演讲中，奥斯本宣布了单个家庭可以从国家获得的福利总额的上限，估计从2013年起每周约500英镑。据估计，这可能导致大约5万失业家庭平均每周损失93英镑。他还宣布，他将结束{{le|儿童福利|Child benefit}}的普遍应享权，以及自2013年起调整所得税率由50%下降到40%。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/oct/04/george-osborne-cap-welfare-payments |title=George Osborne to cap welfare payments |trans_title=奥斯本削减福利开支 |work=The Guardian |location=London |date=4 October 2010 |accessdate=4 October 2010 |first=Helene |last=Mulholland |archive-date=2013-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219131906/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/oct/04/george-osborne-cap-welfare-payments |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 出售诺森罗克银行（2011年） ===

2011年2月，奥斯本宣布了{{le|梅林计划|Project Merlin}}，五大银行[[苏格兰皇家银行|苏格兰皇家银行]]、[[香港上海汇丰银行|香港-上海汇丰银行]]、[[巴克莱银行|巴克莱银行]]、[[劳埃德银行|劳埃德银行]]以及[[桑坦德银行|西班牙桑坦德银行]]计划在2011年为企业提供约1900亿英镑商业贷款（包括760亿英镑给中小型企业），并削减津贴，公示高薪人士的一些工资细节，同时向银行增加征税八亿英镑。自由民主党籍的财政部发言人{{le|马修·奥克肖特|Matthew Oakeshott}}勋爵在协议宣布后辞职。其他承诺包括为首相[[戴维·卡梅伦|戴维·卡梅伦]]的大社会银行项目提供2亿英镑的资本，该银行为社区项目提供资金。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-12402469|title=Banks agree Project Merlin lending and bonus deal|trans_title=银行同意梅林计划：贷款和处理红利|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=3 November 2014|archive-date=2011-02-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110210134202/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-12402469|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2011年11月，奥斯本将[[诺森罗克银行|诺森罗克银行]]以7.47亿到10亿英镑的价格卖给[[理查德·布兰森|理查德·布兰森]]的[[维珍集团|维珍集团]]旗下的维珍金融。<ref name=ind070412>{{cite news |url= http://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/news/osborne-sells-off-northern-rock-for-400m-loss-6264087.html |title= Osborne sells off Northern Rock for £400m loss |trans_title= 奥斯本以四亿英镑的差价出售诺森罗克银行 |author= Nigel Morris |date= 18 November 2011 |newspaper= The Independent |accessdate= 7 April 2012 |archive-date= 2020-01-10 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200110122627/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/news/osborne-sells-off-northern-rock-for-400m-loss-6264087.html |dead-url= no }}</ref>诺森罗克银行是150年来第一家遭受银行挤兑的英国银行，2008年2月被政府收购暂时成为[[公共企业|国营企业]]，然后在2010年1月1日分为两个实体，另一半是{{le|诺森罗克资产管理有限公司|NRAM Limited}}。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hm-treasury.gov.uk/press_116_09.htm |title=Treasury confirms 1 January restructuring of Northern Rock |trans_title=财政部确认1月1日重组诺森罗克 |publisher=HM Treasury |date=8 December 2009 |accessdate=9 December 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091216111947/http://www.hm-treasury.gov.uk/press_116_09.htm |archivedate=2009年12月16日 }}</ref>《[[独立报|独立报]]》报道被卖实体为银行的“断腕”，同时说纳税人仍保留了“200亿英镑的有毒资产的责任，如坏账和封闭按揭”。该交易使银行的净资产价值略低于11.2亿英镑，而对纳税人而言，“铁定最低损失”为3.73亿英镑至4.53亿英镑。<ref name="norock">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/banksandfinance/8903076/George-Osborne-reveals-Northern-Rock-sale-forced-on-him-by-secret-Labour-agreement-with-Brussels.html|title=George Osborne reveals Northern Rock sale forced on him by secret Labour agreement with Brussels|first=|date=20 November 2011|work=|newspaper=The Sunday Telegraph|accessdate=7 April 2012|trans_title=乔治·奥斯本透露原来工党政府与布鲁塞尔的秘密协议强被加给他的诺森罗克出售计划|author=Harry Wilson|archive-date=2020-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122155659/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/banksandfinance/8903076/George-Osborne-reveals-Northern-Rock-sale-forced-on-him-by-secret-Labour-agreement-with-Brussels.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>奥斯本认为这笔交易会得到“比任何其他交易都更让政府受益。”<ref name=ind070412 />并回应了关于时机的担忧，说[[布朗内阁|前工党政府]]和[[布鲁塞尔|布鲁塞尔]][[欧盟委员会|欧盟委员会]]之间的秘密交易要求他们在2013年或之前出售该银行，我们知道至少2012年之前诺森罗克银行会一直亏损，这将进一步耗尽纳税人的资源，同意拍卖计划现在更加迫切。”<ref name="norock" />

=== 2012年 ===

2012年的预算被[[反对党领袖_(英国)|反对党领袖]][[爱德·米利班德|爱德·米利班德]]称为“完全错乱的（Omnishambles）预算”，被认为是奥斯本政治事业的最低点。<ref name="reinvention" /><ref name="faithful" />奥斯本将高收入者的所得税率从50%下调到45%，他说50%这个数字被[[阿利斯泰尔·达林|他的前任]]特意指定为“临时性的”。英国税务及海关总署（HMRC）的数据显示，新税率下的额外税从2012/13年度的380亿英镑增加到2013/14年度的460亿英镑，奥斯本说，这是由于“竞争”更充分。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politicshome.com/economy-and-work/articles/story/cut-top-rate-tax-helped-raise-extra-%C2%A38bn-osborne-claims |title=Cut to top rate of tax helped raise an extra £8bn, Osborne claims |trans_title=奥斯本称，削减高收入者税率会帮助公共财政多筹集80亿英镑|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160302104311/https://www.politicshome.com/economy-and-work/articles/story/cut-top-rate-tax-helped-raise-extra-%C2%A38bn-osborne-claims |archivedate=2 March 2016 }}</ref>

奥斯本因提出对加热出售的食物如[[康沃尔肉馅饼|康沃尔肉馅饼]]征收增值税而受批评。批评者评论了对供应商的潜在影响，以及{{le|财政专责委员会|Treasury Select Committee}}的委员评价奥斯本没有经验的问题，他“不会记得”最后一次从[[Greggs|Greggs]]买肉饼是什么时候。<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.telegraph.co.uk/journalists/rowena-mason/9169900/George-Osborne-cant-remember-eating-in-Greggs-amid-ridicule-over-pasty-tax.html |title= George Osborne 'can't remember' eating in Greggs amid ridicule over pasty tax |trans_title= 乔治·奥斯本不记得在格里格斯吃饭是在什么时候，食品税的嘲笑 |author= Rowena Mason |date= 27 March 2012 |newspaper= The Daily Telegraph |accessdate= 28 March 2012 |archive-date= 2019-06-16 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190616131755/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/journalists/rowena-mason/9169900/George-Osborne-cant-remember-eating-in-Greggs-amid-ridicule-over-pasty-tax.html |dead-url= no }}</ref>{{le|肉饼税|Pasty tax}}的建议后来取消，这被视为是政治上的“{{le|调头|U-turn}}”,以及削减对慈善捐赠和房车屋的税收减免政策。<ref>{{cite news|title=Government confirms U-turn on charity tax|trans_title=政府确认慈善税不成立|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2012/may/31/government-confirms-u-turn-charity-tax|accessdate=28 March 2015|work=The Guardian|date=31 May 2012|archive-date=2015-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150710090749/http://www.theguardian.com/society/2012/may/31/government-confirms-u-turn-charity-tax|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2012年10月，奥斯本提出了一项提高就业的新政策，根据该政策，公司能够提供价值在2000英镑和50000英镑之间的股份给新员工，但受雇人将可能被不合理解雇和失去培训休假的权利。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/george-osborne-workers-of-the-world-unite-and-give-up-your-rights-8202144.html|title=George Osborne: Workers of the world unite... and give up your rights|trans_title=乔治·奥斯本：全世界的工人团结起来...放弃你的权利|work=London Evening Standard|date=8 October 2012|first=Joe|last=Murphy|accessdate=2017-01-29|archive-date=2017-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320151419/http://www.standard.co.uk/news/politics/george-osborne-workers-of-the-world-unite-and-give-up-your-rights-8202144.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/money/2012/oct/08/george-osborne-employee-shares-for-rights|title=George Osborne's 'employee shares for rights' proposal draws scepticism|trans_title=乔治·奥斯本的“雇员权利换股份”提案受到怀疑|work=The Guardian|date=8 October 2012|author1=Mark King|author2=Hilary Osborne|accessdate=2017-01-29|archive-date=2017-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202135524/https://www.theguardian.com/money/2012/oct/08/george-osborne-employee-shares-for-rights|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2012年，奥斯本致函[[美联储|美国联邦储备主席]][[本·伯南克|本·伯南克]]，帮助[[汇丰银行|汇丰银行]]的领导避免刑事指控，因为该银行参与洗钱和向受制裁国家汇款。<ref name="bbc_12July2016"/>奥斯本说，如果汇丰银行在美国失去{{le|银行执照|
banking license}}，这可能对欧洲和亚洲的金融市场产生消极后果。汇丰银行避免了刑事指控，并向美国司法部缴纳了192亿美元的罚款。<ref name="bbc_12July2016">{{cite news|title=HSBC avoided US money laundering charges because of 'market risk' fears|trans_title=汇丰银行因“市场风险”的恐惧而避免了美国政府的洗钱指控|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/business-36768140|accessdate=12 July 2016|publisher=[[BBC|BBC]]|date=12 July 2016|archive-date=2021-01-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210113121513/https://www.bbc.com/news/business-36768140|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 财政赤字 ===

[[File:George_Osborne_in_China.jpg|thumb]]与中国[[国务院副总理|国务院副总理]][[马凯_(官员)|马凯]]会晤]]
2013年2月，英国失去了AAA信用评级（奥斯本在上台时表示自己将竭尽全力保住3A评级），是1978年以来的第一次。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-21557243|title=UK's credit rating cut humiliating, Labour says|trans_title=工党说，英国的信用评级降低是侮辱性的|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=3 November 2014|archive-date=2017-02-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170204202700/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-21557243|dead-url=no}}</ref>他2013年3月的预算是在预算责任办公室对经济增长预测从1.2％下调到0.6％的大背景下产生的。<ref>{{cite news|title=Budget 2013: Economic growth forecast for 2013 halved|trans_title=2013年预算：2013年经济增长预测减半|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-21861322|accessdate=22 March 2016|publisher=BBC News|date=20 March 2013|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308123920/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-21861322|dead-url=no}}</ref>它被《[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]》的经济版编辑描述为“在财政大臣的‘理想英国’的旗帜下的创造性、分散性的满足政策评论员的办法。”<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/budget/9941889/Budget-2013-as-it-happened.html |title=Budget 2013: as it happened |trans_title=2013年预算：发生了 |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=20 March 2013 |accessdate=22 March 2016 |archive-date=2020-11-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122152958/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/budget/9941889/Budget-2013-as-it-happened.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>然而，它受到公众的积极接受，随之而来的是保守党支持率与去年预算公布时的民意调查数据相比明显提高。<ref>{{cite news|title=Budgets, polls and their impact on elections: a brief history|trans_title=预算，民意调查及其对大选的影响：简史|url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/datablog/2015/mar/19/budgets-polls-and-their-impact-on-elections-a-brief-history|accessdate=28 March 2015|work=The Guardian|date=19 March 2015|archive-date=2015-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402225415/http://www.theguardian.com/news/datablog/2015/mar/19/budgets-polls-and-their-impact-on-elections-a-brief-history|dead-url=no}}</ref>经济随后在2013年年中开始回升，奥斯本的公众认可评级在接下来的12个月内从-33升至+3。<ref name="reinvention" />

到2015年3月，年度赤字减少到最初目标的一半左右，因此{{le|债务在GDP中的比率|Debt-to-GDP ratio}}仍在上升。然而，英国国债在这五年间比过去13年（工党执政期间）增加了更多。<ref name="telegraph-20150326">{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/general-election-2015/11494353/National-debt-the-deficit-and-cuts-where-does-each-party-stand-in-General-Election-2015.html |title=National debt, the deficit and cuts: where does each party stand in General Election 2015? |trans_title=国债、赤字和削减：各个党派在2015年大选如何表现？ |author=Asa Bennett |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |date=26 March 2015 |accessdate=2 May 2015 |archive-date=2020-11-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128031748/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/general-election-2015/11494353/National-debt-the-deficit-and-cuts-where-does-each-party-stand-in-General-Election-2015.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

然而，由于[[英国脱欧公投|英国脱欧公投]]造成的不确定性，[[2015年英国大选|大选]]后经济恶化。《[[卫报|卫报]]》在2016年7月回顾了他的在职表现，说英国仍然有4％的预算赤字，国际收支赤字占国内生产总值的7％，而[[意大利|意大利]]则是七国集团中表现最差的。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/jul/17/uk-economy-brexit-failed-economic-policies|title=The fragile UK economy has a chance to abandon failed policies post-Brexit|trans_title=脆弱的英国经济有机会在脱欧后放弃失败的政策|author=Larry Elliott|work=Guardian newspapers|date=17 July 2016|accessdate=24 July 2016|archive-date=2016-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160726222934/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/jul/17/uk-economy-brexit-failed-economic-policies|dead-url=no}}</ref>包括2010-2016年期间的[[英國國家統計局|英国国家统计局]]图表显示贸易赤字的恶化。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ons.gov.uk/economy/nationalaccounts/balanceofpayments/timeseries/hbop/pnbp|title=Source dataset: Balance of Payments time series dataset (PNBP)|trans_title=来源数据集：国际收支时间序列数据集（PNBP）|work=Office for National Statistics|date=30 June 2016|accessdate=3 September 2016|archive-date=2016-09-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160911215411/http://www.ons.gov.uk/economy/nationalaccounts/balanceofpayments/timeseries/hbop/pnbp|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 2015年5月至2016年 ===

在保守党在[[2015年英国大选|2015年大选]]中赢得了大多数席位后，奥斯本在[[卡梅伦第二政府内阁|卡梅伦第二届政府]]中仍任[[财政大臣_(英国)|财政大臣]]。奥斯本还获得了{{le|第一国务大臣|First Secretary of State}}的[[荣誉称号|荣誉称号]]。<ref name="PMO">[https://www.gov.uk/government/news/election-2015-prime-minister-and-ministerial-appointments Election 2015: Prime Minister and ministerial appointments] {{Wayback|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/election-2015-prime-minister-and-ministerial-appointments |date=20150509161531 }} (press release), Prime Minister's Office (8 May 2015).</ref><ref>Nicolas Watts, [https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/may/08/george-osborne-made-first-secretary-of-state-in-cabinet-reshuffle George Osborne made first secretary of state in cabinet reshuffle] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/may/08/george-osborne-made-first-secretary-of-state-in-cabinet-reshuffle |date=20170202135400 }}, ''The Guardian'' (8 May 2015).</ref>

==== 2015年7月预算案 ====

5月16日，奥斯本宣布他将于7月8日提交{{le|英国2015年7月预算|July 2015 United Kingdom budget|第二份预算}}，并承诺通过引入“谷歌税”，旨在阻止大公司因英国的税收政策将利润从英国[[节税|转移出去]]的行动。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-31942639 | publisher=BBC News | title=Budget 2015: 'Google Tax' introduction confirmed | trans_title=2015年预算：“谷歌税”介绍已确认 | date=18 March 2015 | accessdate=2017-01-29 | archive-date=2021-01-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121091759/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-31942639 | dead-url=no }}</ref>此外，大公司现在必须公布他们的英国税务战略，任何坚持从事积极税务规划的大型企业都将被采取特别措施；<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cityam.com/229562/autumn-statement-2015-tax-changes-to-bring-in-5bn-a-year-from-avoidance|title=Autumn Statement 2015: Changes to bring in £5bn a year from tax avoidance|trans_title=2015年秋季报告：每年从避税中带来50亿英镑的变化|accessdate=2017-01-29|archive-date=2016-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160106135130/http://www.cityam.com/229562/autumn-statement-2015-tax-changes-to-bring-in-5bn-a-year-from-avoidance|dead-url=no}}</ref>然而奥斯本因在2003年做客[[英国广播公司第二台|BBC2台]]《Daily Politics》节目时谈论过关于避免遗产税和使用“聪明的金融产品”将房主的财产传给子女的问题，被政治家和记者们广泛批评为虚伪的。<ref>{{cite news|title=Use 'clever financial products', advised George Osborne in 2003 – video|trans_title=使用“聪明的金融产品”，乔治·奥斯本在2003年的建议 - 视频|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/video/2015/feb/16/george-osborne-tax-avoidance-2003-interview-hsbc-video|accessdate=24 January 2016|work=The Guardian|publisher=BBC2 Daily Politics|date=16 February 2015<!-- Original video is from 2003 -->|archive-date=2016-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160130230327/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/video/2015/feb/16/george-osborne-tax-avoidance-2003-interview-hsbc-video|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Mason|first=Rowena|title=Osborne advised using financial loopholes to avoid tax and care costs|trans_title=奥斯本建议使用财务漏洞来避税和护理费用|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/feb/16/osborne-advised-using-financial-loopholes-to-avoid-tax-and-care-costs|accessdate=24 January 2016|work=The Guardian|date=16 February 2015|archive-date=2016-01-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131005201/http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/feb/16/osborne-advised-using-financial-loopholes-to-avoid-tax-and-care-costs|dead-url=no}}<br />{{cite news|last1=Gardner|first1=Kashmira|title=George Osborne advised viewer on how to avoid inheritance tax on The Daily Politics show|trans_title=乔治·奥斯本在节目中传授观众如何避免继承税的技巧|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/george-osborne-advises-viewer-on-how-to-avoid-inheritance-tax-on-the-daily-politics-show-10050347.html|accessdate=24 January 2016|work=The Independent|date=16 February 2015|archive-date=2019-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190617062731/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/george-osborne-advises-viewer-on-how-to-avoid-inheritance-tax-on-the-daily-politics-show-10050347.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

第二个预算案还增加了全国医疗服务的资金，更多的鼓励学徒制，努力提高生产率和削减福利预算。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-32761566|title=George Osborne plans new Budget on 8 July|trans_title=乔治·奥斯本计划7月8日的新预算|publisher=BBC News|date=16 May 2015|accessdate=17 May 2015|archive-date=2021-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111232825/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-32761566|dead-url=no}}</ref>作为回应，保守党领导的{{le|地方政府协会|Local Government Association}}代表375个由保守党、工党或自由民主党掌管的[[英国地方政府|地方议会]]表示，进一步的紧缩措施是“不可选择”的，因为他们会“摧毁”地方服务。他们说，地方议会自2010年以来已经不得不削减40％的开支，如果继续削减，将会对最弱势群体造成严重后果。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2015/may/16/tory-councils-osborne-no-further-austerity|title=No more cuts, Tory councils tell George Osborne|trans_title=没有更多的削减，保守党委员会告诉乔治·奥斯本|work=The Guardian|date=16 May 2015|accessdate=17 May 2015|archive-date=2015-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150516234050/http://www.theguardian.com/society/2015/may/16/tory-councils-osborne-no-further-austerity|dead-url=no}}</ref>在预算制定之后，许多部门被告知要在2019-20年之前将支出削减从25％提高到40％。这使人们担心公共服务会理所当然的被打击，<ref>Preston Robert [[BBC|BBC]] [http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-33609662 Treasury want reinvention of public sector] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-33609662 |date=20201127190246 }}</ref> 并担心保守党在2015年5月大选前的宣言没有清楚解释政策。<ref name=NigelMorris>''[[独立报|独立报]]'' (London) 27 October 2015 [http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/tax-credit-cuts-delayed-by-house-of-lords-hollis-amendment-osborne-a6709846.html Tax credits: House of Lords votes to delay cuts by three years] {{Wayback|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/tax-credit-cuts-delayed-by-house-of-lords-hollis-amendment-osborne-a6709846.html |date=20200706083517 }}</ref>

奥斯本宣布“{{le|1998年国家最低工资法|National Minimum Wage Act 1998|全国最低生活工资}}”到2020年将从7.20英镑/小时上升到9英镑/小时，适用于25岁或以上。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-33437115|title=Budget 2015: Osborne unveils National Living Wage|trans_title=2015年预算，奥斯本提高最低工资|publisher=BBC News|access-date=2017-01-29|archive-date=2020-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204173026/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-33437115|dead-url=no}}</ref>这被保守党议员和政治评论家广泛欢迎。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.publicaffairsnews.com/articles/opinion/jon-craig-osbornes-transition-pantomime-villain-tory-rock-star|title=Jon Craig: Osborne's transition from pantomime villain to Tory rock star|trans_title=乔恩·克雷格：奥斯本从恶棍转变为明星|publisher=publicaffairsnews.com|access-date=2017-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151002043849/https://www.publicaffairsnews.com/articles/opinion/jon-craig-osbornes-transition-pantomime-villain-tory-rock-star|archive-date=2015-10-02|dead-url=yes}}</ref>他还宣布将个人所得税免税额提高至11000英镑；<ref name="sky measures">{{cite web|title=Budget: The Key Points You Need To Know|trans_title=预算：你需要知道的要点|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1515217/budget-the-key-points-you-need-to-know|publisher=[[天空新闻|天空新闻]]|accessdate=8 July 2015|date=8 July 2015|archive-date=2015-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709051233/http://news.sky.com/story/1515217/budget-the-key-points-you-need-to-know|dead-url=no}}</ref>以稅務優惠鼓勵大型公司設立学徒制，目標是到2020年有300万新学徒；并将福利上限削减到伦敦23000英镑，全国其他地区削减到20000英镑。<ref name="sky measures"/>七月份的预算还推迟了2019-2020年度英国财政盈余的到来，并包括在未来五年额外追加180亿英镑的借款。<ref name=liam>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/economics/11733758/George-Osbornes-savvy-display-lacked-tough-fiscal-action.html|title=George Osborne's savvy display lacked tough fiscal action|trans_title=乔治·奥斯本的聪明显示出缺乏强硬的财政措施|author=Liam Halligan|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=11 July 2015|accessdate=12 July 2015|archive-date=2020-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122154015/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/economics/11733758/George-Osbornes-savvy-display-lacked-tough-fiscal-action.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>在7月预算中，奥斯本还计划削减税款抵免，增加低收入工人的薪酬，使人们声称这违反了在5月大选[[英国首相|首相]]卡梅伦做出的承诺。<ref name="r2015">{{cite news|last1=Hattenstone|first1=Simon|title=Cameron shouldn't be allowed to break his tax credit promise. Here's the solution|trans_title=卡梅隆不应该允许别人打破他的税收抵免承诺。这里的解决方案|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/oct/29/manifesto-promise-broken-general-election-david-cameron-child-tax-credits|accessdate=5 March 2016|work=The Guardian|date=29 October 2015|archive-date=2016-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160311100200/http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/oct/29/manifesto-promise-broken-general-election-david-cameron-child-tax-credits|dead-url=no}}</ref>随着公众的反对和上议院投票反对这些变化，奥斯本在2015年秋季声明中废除了这些变更，称高于预期的税收给了他制定政策的更大机动空间。<ref name="sr2015">{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34915218|title=Spending Review: George Osborne scraps cuts to tax credits|trans_title=支出评论：乔治·奥斯本裁减减税额度|accessdate=2017-01-29|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108094944/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-34915218|dead-url=no}}</ref>英国经济智库{{le|财政研究所|Institute for Fiscal Studies}}指出，奥斯本的建议意味着，税款抵免仍将被削减，在2018年改为{{le|通用福利金|Universal Credit}}的一部分。<ref name="r2015" />

==== 金融服务监管局 ====

2015年7月，奥斯本被财政专责委员会工党籍委员[[约翰·曼|约翰·曼]]批评为破坏监管机构的独立性，因为奥斯本解雇了{{le|金融服务监管局|Financial Conduct Authority}}局长{{le|马丁·惠特利|Martin Wheatley}}。惠特利在{{le|支付保护保险|Payment protection insurance}}丑闻之后打击投机欺骗并罚款14亿英镑的行为激怒了银行。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2015/jul/17/city-watchdog-chief-quits-fca-george-osborne|title=City watchdog chief quits after George Osborne vote of no confidence|trans_title=金融城看守市长在奥斯本投票不信任后离职|publisher=The Guardian|author=Phillip Inman|date=17 July 2015|accessdate=24 July 2016|archive-date=2016-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921215817/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2015/jul/17/city-watchdog-chief-quits-fca-george-osborne|dead-url=no}}</ref>奥斯本也因不执行由[[经济合作与发展组织|经济合作与发展组织]]制定的打击避税政策而被批评。<ref name="PEye24/1/16">{{cite news|title=Why multinationals love Generous George|trans_title=为什么跨国公司爱上慷慨的乔治|url=http://www.private-eye.co.uk/in-the-back|accessdate=24 January 2016|work=Private Eye|issue=1410|date=24 January 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160124020802/http://www.private-eye.co.uk/issue-1410/in-the-back|archivedate=24 January 2016}}</ref>2016年1月，当财政部溯及税务协议同意谷歌只补缴过去十年间在英国避税总额的3%被泄露时，[[英国国会议员|议员]]呼吁调查。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mason|first1=Rowena|title=Google tax deal: MPs launch inquiry after criticism of £130m settlement|trans_title=谷歌税协议：议员们在批评1.3亿英镑结算后发起调查|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/jan/25/mps-launch-corporation-tax-inquiry-criticism-130m-google-hmrc-deal|accessdate=5 March 2016|work=The Guardian|date=26 January 2016|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304071227/http://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/jan/25/mps-launch-corporation-tax-inquiry-criticism-130m-google-hmrc-deal|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==== BBC电视许可费 ====

根据《[[卫报|卫报]]》报道，奥斯本是“BBC电视牌照费协议的幕后推手”，BBC將需要為75歲以上人士承擔电视牌照费，意味着它將會损失近20％的收入。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/jul/06/osborne-slashes-bbc-budget-pay-over-75s-tv-licences|title=George Osborne forces BBC to pay for over-75s' TV licences|trans_title=乔治·奥斯本强迫BBC承担75岁以上人士电视牌照费|author=Jane Martinson and John Plunkett|work=Guardian Newspapers|date=6 July 2015|accessdate=19 December 2015|archive-date=2015-12-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151218174457/http://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/jul/06/osborne-slashes-bbc-budget-pay-over-75s-tv-licences|dead-url=no}}</ref>《卫报》还指出，奥斯本与[[新闻集团|新闻集团]]的代表举行了四次会议，并在宣布協議之前与[[鲁伯特·默多克|默多克]]公司举行了两次会议。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/dec/18/george-osborne-rupert-murdoch-bbc-cuts-news-corp|title=George Osborne met Rupert Murdoch twice before imposing BBC cuts|trans_title=乔治·奥斯本在迫使BBC裁员之前会见了默多克两次|author=Jasper Jackson and Jane Martinson|work=Guardian Newspapers|date=18 December 2015|accessdate=19 December 2015|archive-date=2015-12-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151218174457/http://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/dec/18/george-osborne-rupert-murdoch-bbc-cuts-news-corp|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==== 2016年预算 ====

在奥斯本的2016年预算中，他推出了糖税，将所得税免税额提高到11500英镑，并将40％的所得税门槛提高到45000英镑。他还为几个大型基础设施项目提供了初期资金，如{{le|3号高速铁路|High Speed 3}}（横跨英格兰北部的东西铁路干线）、{{le|2号十字铁路|Crossrail 2}}（跨越伦敦的南北铁路线）和[[英国M62高速公路|M62号高速公路]]中一条贯穿[[奔宁山脉|奔宁山脉]]的隧道升级维护。<ref name=budgetpoints>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-35819797|title=Budget 2016 summary: Key points at-a-glance|trans_title=预算2016年摘要：关键点一目了然|access-date=2017-01-29|archive-date=2021-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125021413/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-35819797|dead-url=no}}</ref>并为40岁以下的英国公民提供新的“终生”个人储蓄账户（ISA），每节省4英镑就能得到1英镑。那些每年为住房储蓄省下4000英镑的人，政府承诺在他们50岁之前每年为他们的账户充值1000英镑。<ref name=budgetpoints/> 还有1亿英镑用于解决露宿者。<ref>{{ cite web|url=https://www.politicshome.com/home-affairs/articles/story/george-osborne-announce-£100m-tackle-homelessness|title=George Osborne to announce £100m to tackle homelessness|trans_title=乔治奥斯本宣布1亿英镑解决无家可归者|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160321022029/https://www.politicshome.com/home-affairs/articles/story/george-osborne-announce-%C2%A3100m-tackle-homelessness|archivedate=2016-03-21}}</ref>然而，许多慈善机构抱怨说，他们认为奥斯本的2016年预算有利于大企业，而不是残疾人。<ref>''[[独立报|独立报]]'' (London) 17 March 2016 [http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/george-osborne-budget-disabled-children-big-business-a6934521.html George Osborne put big business ahead of children and disabled people in his Budget, charities say] {{Wayback|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/george-osborne-budget-disabled-children-big-business-a6934521.html |date=20201108130321 }}</ref>

到2016年8月，已有超過50万人开立了新个人储蓄账户希望作为住房储蓄使用，结果卻发现要等到房產交易完成後始会支付奖金，这个缺陷曝光后，奥斯本被[[每日邮报|每日邮报]]批评，导致专家称该计划是“无用”和“骗局”。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/08/19/help-to-buy-isa-scandal-500000-first-time-buyers-told-scheme-can/|title=Help to Buy Isa scandal:500,000 first time buyers told scheme cannot be used for initial deposit on homes|trans_title=购房援助计划个人储蓄账户丑闻：50万人第一次使用时买方告知方案不能用于首次住房储蓄|author=Katie Morley|work=Daily Telegraph|date=19 August 2016|accessdate=20 August 2016|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125175509/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/08/19/help-to-buy-isa-scandal-500000-first-time-buyers-told-scheme-can/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 回到后座 ==

2016年7月13日，[[特蕾莎·梅|特蕾莎·梅]]任首相之后，奥斯本被解雇，外交大臣[[菲利普·哈蒙德|菲利普·哈蒙德]]取代他成为财政大臣。奥斯本回到后座。<ref>Laura Hughes, [http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/07/13/prime-minister-theresa-may-makes-new-cabinet-appointments---as-b/ Theresa May's Cabinet reshuffle: Boris Johnson appointed Foreign Secretary as George Osborne is sacked and replaced by Philip Hammond] {{Wayback|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/07/13/prime-minister-theresa-may-makes-new-cabinet-appointments---as-b/ |date=20160713190529 }}. ''The Telegraph'',13 JULY 2016.</ref>2016年8月4日，据透露，奥斯本曾被即将卸任的首相[[戴维·卡梅伦|戴维·卡梅伦]]授予[[名誉勋位|名誉勋位]]。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36976596|title=Osborne tops Ex-PM's honours list|trans_title=奥斯本在前首相的授勋名单中|date=4 August 2016|access-date=4 August 2016|website=BBC News|archive-date=2016-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030013054/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-36976596|dead-url=no}}</ref>与卡梅伦不同，奥斯本打算在2020年连任国会议员，虽然他的塔顿选区可能在拟议的选区边界变化后消失。在2016年9月，他发起了{{le|北方经济引擎|Northern Powerhouse}}合作伙伴关系，这是一个聚集商业领袖和政治家以促进区域经济发展和权力下放的机构。<ref>{{cite news |title=George Osborne to chair Northern Powerhouse Partnership |trans_title=奥斯本任北方经济引擎合作伙伴关系主席 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/sep/16/george-osborne-to-chair-northern-powerhouse-partnership |first=Heather |last=Stewart |work=The Guardian |date=16 September 2016 |accessdate=2017-01-29 |archive-date=2017-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170126092737/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/sep/16/george-osborne-to-chair-northern-powerhouse-partnership |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Dinner with the FT: George Osborne |trans_title=与金融时报的晚餐：乔治·奥斯本 |url=https://www.ft.com/content/26483056-7fe9-11e6-8e50-8ec15fb462f4 |first=George |last=Parker |work=Financial Times |date=23 September 2016 |accessdate=2017-01-29 |archive-date=2017-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122064714/https://www.ft.com/content/26483056-7fe9-11e6-8e50-8ec15fb462f4 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

奥斯本也成为{{le|麦凯恩国际领导力研究所|McCain Institute}}研究员。尽管该研究所位于美国[[亚利桑那州|亚利桑那州]]，但他仍会留在伦敦办公。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jan/30/george-osborne-john-mccain-institute-academic-job|title=George Osborne takes up academic job at McCain Institute|last=correspondent|first=Peter Walker Political|date=2017-01-30|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=2017-11-28|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111234219/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/jan/30/george-osborne-john-mccain-institute-academic-job|dead-url=no}}</ref>

到2016年10月，他正在写一本名为《不合理的时代》的书；它是对“[[民粹|民粹]]民族主义”的讽刺。<ref name="dailytelegraphsayscapitalism">{{cite news|last1=Hughes|first1=Laura|title=George Osborne says capitalism and democracy are 'in crisis' as he announces new book|trans_title=乔治·奥斯本说，资本主义和民主在“危机”中，他宣布新书|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/06/george-osborne-says-capitalism-and-democracy-are-in-crisis-as-he/|accessdate=October 8, 2016|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=October 6, 2016|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125182840/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/06/george-osborne-says-capitalism-and-democracy-are-in-crisis-as-he/|dead-url=no}}</ref>奥斯本被解雇后，他因经常出席金融企业的会议发表演讲而获得丰厚回报，使他成为2016年收入最高的国会议员。<ref>{{cite news |title=George Osborne named as highest earning MP of 2016 |trans_title=乔治·奥斯本被评为2016年最高收入的国会议员 |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/george-osborne-highest-paid-richest-mp-parliament-how-much-earn-uk-politicians-a7498696.html |first=Rachel |last=Roberts |work=The Independent |date=28 December 2016 |accessdate=2017-01-29 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111174213/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/george-osborne-highest-paid-richest-mp-parliament-how-much-earn-uk-politicians-a7498696.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>在2017年2月，他将开始担任世界上最大的基金经理公司[[贝莱德|贝莱德]]的兼职顾问。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/business-38696175|title=Osborne to join investment giant BlackRock as adviser|trans_title=奥斯本加入投资巨头贝莱德作为顾问|date=20 January 2017|work=BBC News|language=en-GB|access-date=21 January 2017|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112030911/https://www.bbc.com/news/business-38696175|dead-url=no}}</ref>这需要英国{{le|商业任命咨询委员会|Advisory Committee on Business Appointments}}的批准，奥斯本任财政大臣期间被认为“没有具体的政策决定……会影响贝莱德”，财政部常务秘书表示对奥斯本的任命“不担心”。<ref>{{cite magazine |last= |first= |date=27 January 2017 |title=Treasury jest |trans_title=财政部笑话|url= |magazine=Private Eye |location=London |publisher=Pressdram Ltd |access-date=27 January 2017}}</ref>

